<topic template="Default" modified="2020-06-15T16:13:17.994+03:00" lasteditedby="User1" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Initializing a component</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Initializing a component</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">Component is a custom HTML-element which consists of its inner markup, styles for this markup, and a JavaScript class that defines the behavior. Import it on the page and use a dedicated HTML tag to add it to the slide.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.70; background-color:#ffffff; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.70; background-color:#ffffff; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Heading3" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#585858; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;" translate="true">How to Initialize a Component</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">You can create components in folders with presentation or in separate folders. In this tutorial we will create a component in the presentation folder.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">1. Log in to the system by running the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#c7254e; background-color:#f9f2f4;" translate="true">co login</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true"> command, enter your eWizard instance and credentials. You can run this command in any folder you want, but let&apos;s create a folder name </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#c7254e; background-color:#f9f2f4;" translate="true">my-presentation</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true"> and run the command there:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#cacaca; background-color:#272822;" translate="true">D:\my-presentation&gt; co login</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">2. After that, run the following command to initialize the presentation:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#cacaca; background-color:#272822;" translate="true">D:\my-presentation&gt; co init</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">3. Create a folder for your component (not in the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">node_modules</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true"> directory, as there it can be incidentally deleted) and run the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#c7254e; background-color:#f9f2f4;" translate="true">co comp init</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true"> command:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#cacaca; background-color:#272822;" translate="true">D:\my-presentation\app\greeting&gt; co comp init</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">4. You will be prompted about the additional information about the component (name, category, description and some others). You can enter the required information or just leave everything by default.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">5. As a result, the command creates the initial component structure which looks the following way:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><image src="greeting.png" scale="100.00%" padding="0 0 1 0" styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-size:12pt;"></image></para>
  </body>
